al to meet their obligations as they come due. The Company=E2=80=99s due di=
ligence procedures for its lending activities may include review of the fin=
ancial position of the borrower, liquidity levels of the borrower in applic=
able assets, review of the borrower=E2=80=99s management, review of certain=
